EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A boundary across the area triggered thunderstorms in east Tennessee during the afternoon and evening hours.  A few became severe producing large hail and damaging thunderstorm wind.
EVENT_NARRATIVE: A trained spotter reported thunderstorms produced quarter-size hail in Kingsport.

EPISODE_NARRATIVE: An intense area of low pressure which moved from Indiana north across the Great Lakes, produced damaging winds over parts of eastern New York during the afternoon of December 1.  The wind downed trees and power lines in Warren, Washington, Saratoga, Schenectady, Albany, Rensselaer, Schoharie, Greene and Dutchess Counties.  Damage was most widespread in Saratoga, Warren and Rensselaer Counties.  At Waterford in Saratoga County, a tree fell on a trailer home and truck.  Approximately 2,000 customers lost power in the Capital District.
